<dl id="n40078c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40078c">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40078c"> 78(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hadis</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A Hadis attributed to Mohammed runs, &ldquo;They (women) lack wits and faith. When Eve was created Satan rejoiced.&rdquo; <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 193</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: A Hadis, or more commonly Hadith, is an item from the collected sayings and deeds of the Islamic prophet. </mm> </dd></dl>
